odegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | — | — |\n| `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | — | — |\n| `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none — scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | — | — |\n| `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` → `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n| `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n| `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` → `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | — | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/design.md","time":{"start":1775876702473,"end":1775876702479}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775876702494,"sessionID":"ses_28580a87affed4Unrh8BD3JLL6","part":{"id":"prt_d7a800110001wO1Tsw9Y7kpv1V","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a7fee19001N9v26XeA3JU2iI","sessionID":"ses_28580a87affed4Unrh8BD3JLL6","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":21850,"input":1805,"output":87,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":19958}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775876708058,"sessionID":"ses_28580a87affed4Unrh8BD3JLL6","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8016d7001aEaZ6RJPGS6P8W","messageID":"msg_d7a800134001M86Oadx0r7Fg5i","sessionID":"ses_28580a87affed4Unrh8BD3JLL6","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775876712962,"sessionID":"ses_28580a87affed4Unrh8BD3JLL6","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8027ed001ARtm3IWQnghvzA","messageID":"msg_d7a800134001M86Oadx0r7Fg5i","sessionID":"ses_28580a87affed4Unrh8BD3JLL6","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the information needed. Let me create the comprehensive delta-spec.md:","time":{"start":1775876712960,"end":1775876712960}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876752639,"sessionID":"ses_28580a87affed4Unrh8BD3JLL6","part":{"id":"prt_d7a802a03001otMkwUZIDPx22b","messageID":"msg_d7a800134001M86Oadx0r7Fg5i","sessionID":"ses_28580a87affed4Unrh8BD3JLL6","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_42cd0138edec49ecb6922381","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis AR implements 12 GitHub Actions workflows to automate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-034\n- **Module**: `.github`\n- **Language**: `YAML`\n- **Size**: L\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Build Verification\n\n### AR-034-001: Docker build in CI\n\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n- **WHEN** the \"Agentcube CI Workflow\" (main.yml) runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n- **AND** SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Lint and Code Quality\n\n### AR-034-002: Go lint on changed Go code\n\n- **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n- **WHEN** the Lint workflow (lint.yml) runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint` using golangci-lint\n\n### AR-034-003: Python lint with Ruff\n\n- **GIVEN** path filter matches `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`\n- **WHEN** the Python Lint job runs with Python `3.10`\n- **THEN** it SHALL `pip install ruff` and run `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n\n### AR-034-004: Spelling check with codespell\n\n- **GIVEN** checkout complete on a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the Codespell workflow runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL temporarily backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json` at repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n- **AND** SHALL use `pip install codespell` and run codespell with `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on `.`\n- **AND** SHALL restore backed-up files after check completes\n\n### AR-034-005: Copyright header check\n\n- **GIVEN** path filter marks `copyright` (all paths minus exclusions for `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**`)\n- **WHEN** the Copyright Check workflow runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (`sponge`), run `make gen-copyright`, and execute `git diff --exit-code`\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Code Generation\n\n### AR-034-006: Code generation verification\n\n- **GIVEN** path filter matches `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n- **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs with Go `1.24.4`\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `make gen-check` which executes `make gen-all` and `git diff --exit-code`\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Testing\n\n### AR-034-007: Go test coverage reporting\n\n- **GIVEN** path filter `coverage` matches (broad glob excluding some media/docs per workflow) on a pull request or merge group\n- **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n- **AND** SHALL upload `coverage.out` as an artifact\n- **AND** SHALL optionally upload to Codecov when `CODECOV_TOKEN` is present\n\n### AR-034-008: End-to-end testing on Kind\n\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n- **WHEN** the E2E workflow (e2e.yml) runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n- **AND** SHALL install Kind tool v0.30.0 using `helm/kind-action@v1` with `install_only: true`\n- **AND** SHALL run `make e2e` with Go `1.23`\n- **AND** SHALL upload `e2e-logs/` directory on failure\n- **AND** SHALL always run `make e2e-clean` to clean up resources\n\n### AR-034-009: Python SDK unit tests\n\n- **GIVEN** path filter matches `sdk-python/**`\n- **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests job runs with Python `3.12` in `sdk-python/`\n- **THEN** it SHALL `pip install pytest`\n- **AND** SHALL `pip install -e .` (editable install)\n- **AND** SHALL run `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Release and Publication\n\n### AR-034-010: Release image publication\n\n- **GIVEN** a `push` event to `main` branch or semantic version tags (`v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*`)\n- **WHEN** the Build and Push Release Images workflow runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL determine `TAG` - if `github.ref_type` is `tag`, `TAG` SHALL be `github.ref_name`; otherwise `TAG` SHALL be `latest`\n- **AND** SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` with `GITHUB_TOKEN`\n- **AND** SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push` for workloadmanager, `docker-buildx-push-router` for router, and `docker-buildx-push-picod` for picod\n- **AND** SHALL set `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and per-image `*_IMAGE=<name>:${TAG}`\n\n### AR-034-011: Dify plugin publish\n\n- **GIVEN** a push event with tags matching `dify-plugin/v*`\n- **WHEN** the Dify Plugin Publish workflow runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6 and install `yq`\n- **AND** SHALL read `manifest.yaml` and package the plugin as `.difypkg`\n- **AND** SHALL checkout `author/dify-plugins` repository with token\n- **AND** SHALL move `.difypkg` to the repository\n- **AND** SHALL create a branch, commit, push, and create a PR to `langgenius/dify-plugins`\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Workflow Automation\n\n### AR-034-012: First-time contributor workflow approval\n\n- **GIVEN** a `pull_request_target` event with types `labeled` or `synchronize` on `main` or `release-**` branches\n- **WHEN** a contributor is not first-time (more than one PR merged) or PR has `ok-to-test` label\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required`\n- **AND** SHALL call `approveWorkflowRun` for each pending run\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- AgentCube proposal: `changes/AR-034/proposal.md`\n- CI/CD design: `ci-cd/design.md`\n- CI/CD spec: `ci-cd/spec.md`\n- GitHub Actions documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/actions\n\n(End of file)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775876752614,"end":1775876752636}}}}
